---
// Editor's Note — a small framed editorial aside between sections.
---

<aside class="editors-note" aria-label="A note from the editor">
  <div class="inner">
    <div class="head">
      <p class="eyebrow">From the Editor</p>
      <div class="rule"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="body">
      <p>
        This issue introduces KnitTools: a full toolkit for Android. Counters, scanners, calculators,
        reference charts, and AI that reads patterns aloud. All under one roof, paid for once, ever.
        No subscription, no account, no trial that quietly turns into a charge.
      </p>
      <p>
        The pre-launch list opens through the season. Signing up locks in the launch price for good,
        and guarantees a note on the day the app ships. No other emails in between.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</aside>

<style>
  .editors-note {
    background: var(--paper);
    padding: 80px 40px;
  }
  .inner {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 28px 0 26px;
    border-top: 3px double var(--ink);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink);
    position: relative;
  }

  .head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 22px;
  }
  .eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.24em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--terracotta);
    margin: 0;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .rule {
    flex: 1;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--ink);
    opacity: 0.5;
  }

  .body p {
    font-family: var(--body-ed);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }
  .body p:last-of-type { margin-bottom: 0; }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .editors-note { padding: 56px 20px; }
    .inner { padding: 28px 24px 24px; }
    .body p { font-size: 15px; }
  }
</style>
